  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      evaluate the safety of preoperative aspirin therapy when performing bypass surgery in
      conditions of artificial blood circulation
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The hypothesis of the study was that aspirin therapy started 24 hours before CABG is safe.

      The effectiveness of this hypothesis will be assessed by the presence of a 30-day period
      after CABG myocardial infarction, ischemic stroke, repeat revascularizations
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
