        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients 18 years of age or older

          -  Patient able to give informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Missing consent

          -  Urgent or emergent surgery

          -  Off-pump CABG

          -  Ð atient has clear indication for anticoagulation (eg. mechanical heart valve, atrial
             fibrillation) or ADP receptor antagonist (eg. drug-eluting stent)

          -  History of bleeding diathesis, significant GI bleed, ICH, or liver failure

          -  Allergy to or intolerance of aspirin
      </textblock>
